MEDIABOARD README
<jagwire>



INSTALLATION OF MEDIABOARD
The installation of the mediaboard requires installation of the javacv
libraries. Please see the README in wonderland-modules/unstable/javacv-integration
for more information and installation instructions. The mediaboard camera
functionality WILL NOT WORK without the javacv-integration libraries installed.

In addition, a server wanting to use the mediaboard should:
* Have authentication enabled
* A group entitled "media" should be created, and all users added
* Have a groups/ directory added to the content folder on the server
--This can be done via the web administration page
* Inside the groups/ directory, there should be a media directory
added.

********************
* IMPORTANT!!!!    *
********************
Double check that via the "Manage content" tab in the web administration
page that you can see the following links: 
* checksums
* groups
* modules
* system
* users

When clicking the groups link, make sure you can see the following links:
* media

When clicking the media link, make sure you can see the following links:
* boards
* images
* photos
* videos

